cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with mining and monitoring darknet traffic to detect emerging threats and malicious campaigns. It also involves handling large streams of logs and representing traffic patterns in a meaningful way, which are common tasks in the field of cybersecurity. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper deals with network packets and ports, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it uses Word2Vec for learning the meaning of targeted network ports, cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves clustering and time-series analysis, and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with analyzing network traffic and behavior.
